    <h1>Security Guidelines</h1>
    <p>Source: <a href="http://web.missouri.edu/~reissingr/2008%20UI%20Guidelines/" target="_blank">http://web.missouri.edu/~reissingr/2008%20UI%20Guidelines/</a></p>
    
    <p>Applications should be consistent in both appearance and behavior. Commands, visual presentation and element placement should all be consistent throughout the entire application and from application to application.</p>
    
    <p>Users will learn applications faster when the interfaces look and behave like applications they have already used. Consistency also reduces the workload for developers by allowing re-use of design components and easier transfer of knowledge and skills between developers.</p>
    
    <p>All Division of IT applications are to follow these basic guidelines.</p>
    
